Just visited the site and huh? What an odd format. Let me get this straight: you either pay individually for random workouts, OR for a series of workouts ranging from 2 to 10 or so, OR there are monthly subscriptions for certain trainers? I think that’s what I saw, anyway.

First of all, it’s extremely confusing. Secondly, why would I pay such premium prices for one workout or a few workouts when I could either
1. Pay monthly on a site or an app for many workouts or
2. Stay with someone like FitnessBlender that has tons of free workouts or where you can pay $9.99 for multiple 30 day workout series that are super effective (and that you only pay for once)?

I’m not sure where you guys got this convoluted idea from but it doesn’t seem like it’s been well thought out at all. There are so many legitimate workout sites already where I can pay a set amount for a lot of workouts. What exactly is the benefit here?

Everyone has different preferences. I like Fitness Blender, but I had to stop for several reasons that I don't need to go into here. I am super excited about GLOW b/c there are so many different workouts by amazing instructors. I am pretty sure that it will be well worth the money. Whatever you decide, good luck with your fitness journey!
